H0.text: Osmosis most likely occurs across a permeable membrane that separates solutions of the same concentration in cells.

H1.text: Osmosis would most likely occur across a permeable membrane that separates solutions of different concentrations in cells.

H2.text: Osmosis most likely occurs across a nonpermeable membrane that separates solutions of the same concentration in cells.

H3.text: Osmosis most likely occurs across a nonpermeable membrane that separates solutions of different concentrations in cells.

A4.text: If the medium is hypotonic relative to the cell cytoplasm, the cell will gain water through osmosis.

A5.text: If the medium is isotonic, there will be no net movement of water across the cell membrane.
